    "body": "Resolves #39431 \r\n\r\nAdd `vim.ui.img.supported()`, which queries the terminal via kitty APC to detect graphics protocol support. Update the vim.ui.img health check to use this API and simplify the tmux check to a plain warning.\r\n\r\n### Supported\r\n\r\nDid this with ghostty\r\n\r\n<img width=\"1854\" height=\"384\" alt=\"image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/b9144d07-d67a-45c6-b8cb-f958534b589c\" />\r\n\r\n### Unsupported\r\n\r\nDid this with Mac terminal. Notice that the APC code we send shows up at the top. I'm not sure of the best way to clear this. If you do something like `:mode` in the healthcheck, it goes away.\r\n\r\n<img width=\"1128\" height=\"236\" alt=\"image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/35850f14-5cc9-4140-a4d1-019d1345bebe\" />\r\n\r\n\r\n### Tmux message\r\n\r\nFrom tmux running in ghostty, ended up showing both the error and the warning, which I think makes it pretty clear.\r\n\r\n<img width=\"900\" height=\"250\" alt=\"image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/85f366b2-e48e-4098-abb0-896b42afae85\" />\r\n\r\n",
    "closed_at": null,
