            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "@gpanders @justinmk I was originally going to use the tty.lua:query until I saw that it only does XTGETTCAP. I didn't want to break anything by trying to rewrite it to support both.\r\n\r\nSo was sticking with yet another copy and meant to mention it, but forgot. You guys are too quick for me :)\r\n\r\n@justinmk you want me to move it as a separate query for now? I was hiding it as an implementation detail of kitty.",
            "commit_id": "15487a1823d231391703c3981e081c6fff2203c5",
            "created_at": "2026-04-27T21:00:30Z",
            "diff_hunk": "@@ -147,4 +147,69 @@ function M.delete(img_id)\n   }))\n end\n \n+--- Query whether this terminal supports the kitty graphics protocol.\n+--- Blocks until the terminal responds or times out.\n+---\n+---@param opts? {timeout?: integer} timeout in milliseconds (default: 1000)\n+---@return boolean supported\n+---@return string? msg error detail if terminal responded but not with OK\n+function M.supported(opts)\n+  local timeout = opts and opts.timeout or 1000\n+  local query_id = generate_id()\n+  local timer = assert(vim.uv.new_timer())\n+\n+  ---@type boolean?\n+  local result\n+  ---@type string?\n+  local msg\n+\n+  local id = vim.api.nvim_create_autocmd('TermResponse', {",
